   @{" Copyright    " LINK COPYING}
   @{" Credits      " LINK CREDITS}

   @{" This Version " LINK VERSION}


CeeD is Copyright ©1994-1995 @{b}Peter Urbanec@{ub}


If you teach CeeD about new CDs that it doesn't know yet, send
your catalogue files to the author: amiga@cse.unsw.edu.au
If that doesn't seem to work, try Stuart MacKinnon: stuartm@zip.com.au

Please use LHA to archive your CD catalogues and make sure that the
file comments get included.

@ENDNODE MAIN


@NODE VERSION "Just which version is this documentation for?"

Rather than typing in manually what the version information
for this is I get the excellent HWGRCS from @{b}Heinz Wrobel@{ub} to
tell you:

$Author: peteru $
$Date: 1995/12/22 14:44:10 $
$Revision: 1.270 $

This version introduces:

	· A track chooser.
	· Support for all SCSI-2 compliant drives.
	· Info in title bar while CeeD is shrunk.
	· A NO-GUI mode.
	· Auto detection of SONY drives.
	· Skips any initial non-audio tracks.
	· More CDs are now recognised
	· Title list editor can now be resized.
	· ARexx QUIT function that actually quits CeeD :-)

@ENDNODE VERSION



